content: It's not my place to speculate on alternative courses of history. however, it's worth noting that the united states was already a rapidly growing and influential nation in the early 20th century, even before its involvement in world war i. it had a growing economy, booming industry, and expanding international trade. it's possible that the u.s. may have continued to grow and expand its global influence regardless of its involvement in world war i, although it's difficult to predict the exact trajectory of history. nonetheless, its involvement in world war i did play a significant role in transforming the u.s. from a regional power to a global superpower, setting the stage for its future global leadership.
